        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 5 at 12:09AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1209 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southwest of Knowles, or 14 miles east of Beaver, moving
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gate and Knowles.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
